def weighted_batch(X_train, y_train, X_test, y_test, min_weight=0, step=0.1, min_threshold=0.1, max_threshold=0.9):
  """
  Fonction pour dterminer le meilleur stacking des modles prdictifs
  """
  len_x_train = len(X_train)
  best_scores = [[0, 0, 0, 0] for x in range(3)]

  best_scores = _rec_best_weights(X_train, y_train, X_test, y_test, best_scores, min_weight, step, cpt=len_x_train)

  return best_scores

def _best_scores_thresholds(x_train, y_train, x_test, y_test, prev_scores, list_weight, min_threshold=0.1, max_threshold=0.8):
  """
  Dtermine le meilleur seuil pour la meilleure prdiction
  """
  for i in np.arange(min_threshold, max_threshold, 0.1):
      i = round(i, 2)
      x_train_thre = x_train.copy()
      x_test_thre = x_test.copy()
      x_train_thre[x_train_thre >= i] = 1
      x_train_thre[x_train_thre < i] = 0
      x_test_thre[x_test_thre >= i] = 1
      x_test_thre[x_test_thre < i] = 0
      acc_train_preds = accuracy_score(x_train_thre, y_train)
      acc_test_preds = accuracy_score(x_test_thre, y_test)
      f1_test_preds = f1_score(x_test_thre, y_test, average='micro')

      if acc_train_preds > prev_scores[0][1]:
        prev_scores[0][0] = (i,) + tuple(list_weight)
        prev_scores[0][1] = acc_train_preds
        prev_scores[0][2] = acc_test_preds
        prev_scores[0][3] = f1_test_preds
      if acc_test_preds > prev_scores[1][2]:
        prev_scores[1][0] = (i,) + tuple(list_weight)
        prev_scores[1][1] = acc_train_preds
        prev_scores[1][2] = acc_test_preds
        prev_scores[1][3] = f1_test_preds
      if f1_test_preds > prev_scores[2][3]:
        prev_scores[2][0] = (i,) + tuple(list_weight)
        prev_scores[2][1] = acc_train_preds
        prev_scores[2][2] = acc_test_preds
        prev_scores[2][3] = f1_test_preds

  return prev_scores

def _rec_best_weights(X_train, y_train, X_test, y_test, best_scores, min_weight=0, step=0.1, list_weight=[], cpt=0):
  """
  Mthode utilise pour effectuer chaque combinaison possible de stacking
  """
  alpha = sum(list_weight)

  if cpt == 1:
      list_weight += [round(1-alpha, 2)]
      x_train = np.sum([w*l for w, l in zip(list_weight, X_train)], axis=0)
      x_test = np.sum([w*l for w, l in zip(list_weight, X_test)], axis=0)
      best_scores = _best_scores_thresholds(x_train, y_train, x_test, y_test, best_scores, list_weight)
      
      return best_scores
  else:
    cpt -= 1

    for beta in np.arange(min_weight, round(1 - alpha + step - min_weight, 2), step):
      beta = round(beta, 2)
      best_scores = _rec_best_weights(X_train, y_train, X_test, y_test, best_scores, min_weight, step, list_weight + [beta], cpt)
    
    return best_scores

In practice, why would different compilers compute different values of int x = ++i + ++i;? In practice, why would different compilers compute different values of int x = ++i + ++i;? <p>Consider this code:</p>

<pre><code>int i = 1;
int x = ++i + ++i;
</code></pre>

<p>We have some guesses for what a compiler might do for this code, assuming it compiles.</p>

<ol>
<li>both <code>++i</code> return <code>2</code>, resulting in <code>x=4</code>.</li>
<li>one <code>++i</code> returns <code>2</code> and the other returns <code>3</code>, resulting in <code>x=5</code>.</li>
<li>both <code>++i</code> return <code>3</code>, resulting in <code>x=6</code>.</li>
</ol>

<p>To me, the second seems most likely. One of the two <code>++</code> operators is executed with <code>i = 1</code>, the <code>i</code> is incremented, and the result <code>2</code> is returned. Then the second <code>++</code> operator is executed with <code>i = 2</code>, the <code>i</code> is incremented, and the result <code>3</code> is returned. Then <code>2</code> and <code>3</code> are added together to give <code>5</code>.</p>

<p>However, I ran this code in Visual Studio, and the result was <code>6</code>. I'm trying to understand compilers better, and I'm wondering what could possibly lead to a result of <code>6</code>. My only guess is that the code could be executed with some "built-in" concurrency. The two <code>++</code> operators were called, each incremented <code>i</code> before the other returned, and then they both returned <code>3</code>. This would contradict my understanding of the call stack, and would need to be explained away.</p>

<p>My question is: what (reasonable) things could a <code>C++</code> compiler do that would lead to a result of <code>4</code> or a result or <code>6</code>?</p>

La lemmatisation est utilise avec d'autres traitements :

  • Elimination des tags HTLM, ponctuations
  • Transformation des majuscules en minuscules
  • Les ponctuations dans C++, C# sont conservs
  • Les mots avec un seul mot sont supprims sauf pour R et C

Le tout est fait avec de la paralllisation pour acclrer le temps de calcul

In [ ]:
punctuations = re.sub("[+#]", "", string.punctuation)
keep_letters = ["r", "c"]
stopw = list(set(stopw + [x.translate(str.maketrans("", "", "'")) for x in stopw]))

lemmatizer = WordNetLemmatizer()


def get_wordnet_pos(word):
    """
    Fonction employe pour la lemmatisation
    """
    tag = nltk.pos_tag([word])[0][1][0].upper()
    tag_dict = {"J": wordnet.ADJ,
                "N": wordnet.NOUN,
                "V": wordnet.VERB,
                "R": wordnet.ADV}

    return tag_dict.get(tag, wordnet.NOUN)

def txt_preprocessing(text):
    """
    Traitement ligne par ligne
    """
    text = BeautifulSoup(text, 'lxml').get_text()
    text = text.lower()
    text = text.translate(str.maketrans("", "", punctuations))
    text = re.sub("[^c]\+\+|[^\w+](\+|\#)[^\w+]|[\w"+string.punctuation+"]*\d[\w"+string.punctuation+"]*", " ", text)
    text = [w for w in text.split() if (len(w) > 1 or w in keep_letters) and w not in stopw]

    return [lemmatizer.lemmatize(x, get_wordnet_pos(x)) for x in text]    

with Pool() as pool:
    df_stack['Body'] = pool.map(txt_preprocessing, df_stack['Body'])

Pour dterminer le nombre de sujets optimal conserver, vous allons utiliser le score de cohrence.

Dus aux temps d'excution, nous n'allons explore que sur 50, 100, 150 et 200 sujets.

In [ ]:
coherence_values = []
range_topics = [50, 100, 150, 200]
for num_topics in range_topics:
    model = gensim.models.LdaMulticore(bow_corpus, num_topics=num_topics, id2word=dictionary, random_state=1)
    coherencemodel = gensim.models.CoherenceModel(model=model, texts=df_stack['Body'], dictionary=dictionary, coherence='c_v')
    coherence_values.append(coherencemodel.get_coherence())

['c++']
In practice, why would different compilers compute different values of int x = ++i + ++i;?
<p>Consider this code:</p>

<pre><code>int i = 1;
int x = ++i + ++i;
</code></pre>

<p>We have some guesses for what a compiler might do for this code, assuming it compiles.</p>

<ol>
<li>both <code>++i</code> return <code>2</code>, resulting in <code>x=4</code>.</li>
<li>one <code>++i</code> returns <code>2</code> and the other returns <code>3</code>, resulting in <code>x=5</code>.</li>
<li>both <code>++i</code> return <code>3</code>, resulting in <code>x=6</code>.</li>
</ol>

<p>To me, the second seems most likely. One of the two <code>++</code> operators is executed with <code>i = 1</code>, the <code>i</code> is incremented, and the result <code>2</code> is returned. Then the second <code>++</code> operator is executed with <code>i = 2</code>, the <code>i</code> is incremented, and the result <code>3</code> is returned. Then <code>2</code> and <code>3</code> are added together to give <code>5</code>.</p>

<p>However, I ran this code in Visual Studio, and the result was <code>6</code>. I'm trying to understand compilers better, and I'm wondering what could possibly lead to a result of <code>6</code>. My only guess is that the code could be executed with some "built-in" concurrency. The two <code>++</code> operators were called, each incremented <code>i</code> before the other returned, and then they both returned <code>3</code>. This would contradict my understanding of the call stack, and would need to be explained away.</p>

<p>My question is: what (reasonable) things could a <code>C++</code> compiler do that would lead to a result of <code>4</code> or a result or <code>6</code>?</p>

freq_labels = pd.Series([x for item in df_stack['Tags'] for x in item]).value_counts()
labels = freq_labels[:128].index.tolist()

df_stack = df_stack[df_stack['Tags'].astype(bool)]

dictionary = gensim.corpora.Dictionary(df_stack['Body'])
dictionary.filter_extremes(no_below=10, keep_n=20000)
bow_corpus = [dictionary.doc2bow(doc) for doc in df_stack['Body']]
lda_model = gensim.models.LdaMulticore(bow_corpus, num_topics=50, id2word=dictionary, random_state=1)

A l'aide d'une rgression logistique, nous allons effectuer une recherche d'hyperparamtre pour dterminer les meilleurs paramtres pour la construction des TF-IDF en jouant le nombre mininum et maximum de frquence d'apparition d'un mot et la taille maximale du dictionnaire.

In [ ]:
X_train, X_test, y_train, y_test = train_test_split(df_stack['Body'].apply(lambda x : " ".join(x)), df_stack['Tags'], random_state=1, test_size=0.20)
mlb = MultiLabelBinarizer().fit(df_stack['Tags'])
y_train = mlb.transform(y_train)

pipeline = Pipeline([
    ('tfidf', TfidfVectorizer()),
    ('clf', OneVsRestClassifier(LogisticRegression(multi_class='ovr'), n_jobs=-1)),
])
parameters = {    
    'tfidf__min_df': list(range(10, 1000, 50)),
    'tfidf__max_df': [round(x*0.01, 2) for x in list(range(30, 70, 5))],
    'tfidf__max_features': list(range(5000, 30000, 3000))
}

randsearch = RandomizedSearchCV(pipeline, parameters, n_iter=50, cv=ShuffleSplit(n_splits=1, test_size=0.3, random_state=1), n_jobs=-1, verbose=3)
randsearch.fit(X_train, y_train)

print("Meilleurs hyperparamtres :")
print(randsearch.best_params_)

In [ ]:
model = tf.keras.Sequential([
  tf.keras.layers.Embedding(29000, 10),
  tf.keras.layers.Conv1D(128, 3, activation='relu'),
  tf.keras.layers.BatchNormalization(),
  tf.keras.layers.Conv1D(256, 3, activation='relu'),
  tf.keras.layers.BatchNormalization(),
  tf.keras.layers.GlobalAveragePooling1D(),
  tf.keras.layers.Dense(256, activation='relu'),
  tf.keras.layers.Dropout(0.4),
  tf.keras.layers.Dense(128, activation='sigmoid')
])
model.compile(optimizer='adam', loss='binary_crossentropy', metrics=['accuracy'])
history = model.fit(train_padded, y_train, epochs=50, 
                    batch_size=128,
                    validation_split=0.3,
                    callbacks=[tf.keras.callbacks.EarlyStopping('val_loss', patience=3)])

  tf.keras.layers.Embedding(29000, 10),
  tf.keras.layers.LSTM(128, dropout=0.4, return_sequences=True),

Tuning¶

Pour la recherche d'hyperparamtre, un random search est utilis sur :

  • Le nombre maximum de mots
  • La taille utilise pour l'embedding des mots
  • Le nombre de Conv1D, la taille des kernels pour les CNN
  • Le nombre de couches denses
  • Le nombre de neurones par couche
  • Le taux de dropout
  • La taux d'apprentissage
  • Le nombre d'instance par batch
In [ ]:
best_scores = [[0, 0, 0, 0] for x in range(3)]

for cpt in range(25):
  print("Itration n", cpt + 1)
  list_layers = []

  max_words = random.randint(2,6)*5000
  max_words = max_words if max_words < 29000 else 29000
  max_len = random.randint(2,6)*50
  
  tokenizer = Tokenizer(max_words, filters='')
  tokenizer.fit_on_texts(X_train)
  sequences = tokenizer.texts_to_sequences(X_train)
  train_padded_tuning = pad_sequences(sequences, maxlen=int(max_len))
  testing_sequences = tokenizer.texts_to_sequences(X_test)
  test_padded_tuning = pad_sequences(testing_sequences, maxlen=int(max_len))

  len_emb = random.randint(2,4)*5
  list_layers.append(tf.keras.layers.Embedding(max_words, len_emb))

  list_pow_conv1d = []
  power2 = 8
  n_conv1d = random.randint(2, 3)

  for i in range(n_conv1d):
    power2 = random.randint(power2, power2+1) if power2 < 11 else 11
    power = np.power(2, power2)
    kernel = random.randint(2,4)
    list_pow_conv1d.append(power)
    list_layers.append(tf.keras.layers.Conv1D(power, kernel, activation='relu'))
    list_layers.append(tf.keras.layers.BatchNormalization())

  list_layers.append(tf.keras.layers.GlobalAveragePooling1D())

  list_pow_dense = []
  for i in range(random.randint(1, 3)):
    power2 = random.randint(power2-1, power2)
    power = np.power(2, power2)
    list_pow_dense.append((power, round(0.05*(power2+1),2)))
    list_layers.append(tf.keras.layers.Dense(power, activation='relu'))
    list_layers.append(tf.keras.layers.Dropout(0.05*(power2+1)))

  list_layers.append(tf.keras.layers.Dense(128, activation='sigmoid'))

  lr = 10**random.uniform(np.log10(1e-4), np.log10(1e-3))
  nb_batch = np.power(2, random.randint(4, 7))

  print("Max words, len : ({}, {}), Embedding : {}, Size kernel : {}".format(max_words, max_len, len_emb, kernel))
  print("List Conv1d : {}, List dense : {}, Learning rate : {}, Batch : {}".format(list_pow_conv1d, list_pow_dense, lr, nb_batch))

  model = tf.keras.Sequential(list_layers)
  model.compile(optimizer=tf.keras.optimizers.Adam(learning_rate=lr), loss='binary_crossentropy', metrics=['accuracy'])
  model.fit(train_padded_tuning, y_train, epochs=50, 
            batch_size=nb_batch,
            verbose=0,
            validation_split=0.3,
            callbacks=[tf.keras.callbacks.EarlyStopping('val_loss', patience=3)])

  pred_train = model.predict(train_padded_tuning)
  pred_train[pred_train >= 0.5] = 1
  pred_train[pred_train < 0.5] = 0
  pred_test = model.predict(test_padded_tuning)
  pred_test[pred_test >= 0.5] = 1
  pred_test[pred_test < 0.5] = 0

  acc_train = accuracy_score(pred_train, y_train)
  acc_test = accuracy_score(pred_test, y_test)
  f1_test = f1_score(pred_test, y_test, average='micro')
  print('Train : {}, Test : {}, F1_score : {}'.format(acc_train, acc_test, f1_test))
  
  if acc_train > best_scores[0][1]:
    best_scores[0][0] = (max_words, max_len, kernel, len_emb, list_pow_conv1d, list_pow_dense, lr, nb_batch)
    best_scores[0][1] = acc_train
    best_scores[0][2] = acc_test
    best_scores[0][3] = f1_test
  if acc_test > best_scores[1][2]:
    best_scores[1][0] = (max_words, max_len, kernel, len_emb, list_pow_conv1d, list_pow_dense, lr, nb_batch)
    best_scores[1][1] = acc_train
    best_scores[1][2] = acc_test
    best_scores[1][3] = f1_test
  if f1_test > best_scores[2][3]:
    best_scores[2][0] = (max_words, max_len, kernel,len_emb, list_pow_conv1d, list_pow_dense, lr, nb_batch)
    best_scores[2][1] = acc_train
    best_scores[2][2] = acc_test
    best_scores[2][3] = f1_test

  print("-----------")

print("Meilleur taux de succs train :")
print("Combinaison : {}, Train : {}, Test : {}, f1-score : {}".format(best_scores[0][0], best_scores[0][1], best_scores[0][2], best_scores[0][3]))
print("Meilleur taux de succs test :")
print("Combinaison : {}, Train : {}, Test : {}, f1-score : {}".format(best_scores[1][0], best_scores[1][1], best_scores[1][2], best_scores[1][3]))
print("Meilleur F1_score test :")
print("Combinaison : {}, Train : {}, Test : {}, f1-score : {}".format(best_scores[2][0], best_scores[2][1], best_scores[2][2], best_scores[2][3]))

X_train, X_test, y_train, y_test = train_test_split(df_stack['Body'], df_stack['Tags'], random_state=1, test_size=0.20)

tokenizer = Tokenizer(25000, filters='')
tokenizer.fit_on_texts(X_train)
sequences = tokenizer.texts_to_sequences(X_train)
train_padded = pad_sequences(sequences, maxlen=250)
testing_sequences = tokenizer.texts_to_sequences(X_test)
test_padded = pad_sequences(testing_sequences, maxlen=250)

mlb = MultiLabelBinarizer().fit(df_stack['Tags'])
y_train = mlb.transform(y_train)
y_test = mlb.transform(y_test)

model = tf.keras.Sequential([
  tf.keras.layers.Embedding(25000, 10),
  tf.keras.layers.Conv1D(512, 4, activation='relu'),
  tf.keras.layers.BatchNormalization(),
  tf.keras.layers.Conv1D(1024, 4, activation='relu'),
  tf.keras.layers.BatchNormalization(),
  tf.keras.layers.Conv1D(2048, 4, activation='relu'),
  tf.keras.layers.BatchNormalization(),
  tf.keras.layers.GlobalAveragePooling1D(),
  tf.keras.layers.Dense(2048, activation='relu'),
  tf.keras.layers.Dropout(0.6),
  tf.keras.layers.Dense(1024, activation='relu'),
  tf.keras.layers.Dropout(0.55),
  tf.keras.layers.Dense(128, activation='sigmoid')
])
model.compile(optimizer=tf.keras.optimizers.Adam(learning_rate=0.00010858406144880602), loss='binary_crossentropy', metrics=['accuracy'])
history = model.fit(train_padded, y_train, epochs=50, 
                    batch_size=16,
                    validation_split=0.3,
                    callbacks=[tf.keras.callbacks.EarlyStopping('val_loss', patience=3)])

PATH_SAVE = 'drive/My Drive/Colab Notebooks/OC/Projet 5/'

conv1d_ft_model = PATH_SAVE + 'conv1d_ft_model.sav'
model.save(conv1d_ft_model)


pred_train = model.predict(train_padded)
pred_train[pred_train >= 0.5] = 1
pred_train[pred_train < 0.5] = 0
pred_test = model.predict(test_padded)
pred_test[pred_test >= 0.5] = 1
pred_test[pred_test < 0.5] = 0

print('Taux de succs du train {}'.format(accuracy_score(pred_train, y_train)))
print('Taux de succs du test {}'.format(accuracy_score(pred_test, y_test)))
print('f1-score du test {}'.format(f1_score(pred_test, y_test, average='micro')))

best_scores = [[0, 0, 0, 0] for x in range(3)]

for cpt in range(25):
  print("Itration n", cpt + 1)
  list_layers = []

  max_words = random.randint(2,6)*5000
  max_words = max_words if max_words < 29000 else 29000
  max_len = random.randint(2,6)*50
  
  tokenizer = Tokenizer(max_words, filters='')
  tokenizer.fit_on_texts(X_train)
  sequences = tokenizer.texts_to_sequences(X_train)
  train_padded_tuning = pad_sequences(sequences, maxlen=int(max_len))
  testing_sequences = tokenizer.texts_to_sequences(X_test)
  test_padded_tuning = pad_sequences(testing_sequences, maxlen=int(max_len))

  len_emb = random.randint(2,4)*5
  list_layers.append(tf.keras.layers.Embedding(max_words, len_emb))

  list_pow_dense1 = []
  power2 = 8
  n_dense1 = random.randint(2, 3)

  for i in range(n_dense1):
    power2 = random.randint(power2, power2+1) if power2 < 11 else 11

    power = np.power(2, power2)
    list_pow_dense1.append(power)
    list_layers.append(tf.keras.layers.Dense(power, activation='relu'))
    list_layers.append(tf.keras.layers.BatchNormalization())

  list_layers.append(tf.keras.layers.GlobalAveragePooling1D())

  list_pow_dense = []
  for i in range(random.randint(1, 3)):
    power2 = random.randint(power2-1, power2)
    power = np.power(2, power2)
    list_pow_dense.append((power, round(0.05*(power2+1),2)))
    list_layers.append(tf.keras.layers.Dense(power, activation='relu'))
    list_layers.append(tf.keras.layers.Dropout(0.05*(power2+1)))

  list_layers.append(tf.keras.layers.Dense(128, activation='sigmoid'))

  lr = 10**random.uniform(np.log10(1e-4), np.log10(1e-3))
  nb_batch = np.power(2, random.randint(4, 7))

  print("Max words, len : ({}, {}), Embedding : {}".format(max_words, max_len, len_emb))
  print("List dense part 1 : {}, List dense part 2 : {}, Learning rate : {}, Batch : {}".format(list_pow_dense1, list_pow_dense, lr, nb_batch))

  model = tf.keras.Sequential(list_layers)
  model.compile(optimizer=tf.keras.optimizers.Adam(learning_rate=lr), loss='binary_crossentropy', metrics=['accuracy'])
  model.fit(train_padded_tuning, y_train, epochs=50, 
            batch_size=nb_batch,
            verbose=0,
            validation_split=0.3,
            callbacks=[tf.keras.callbacks.EarlyStopping('val_loss', patience=3)])

  pred_train = model.predict(train_padded_tuning)
  pred_train[pred_train >= 0.5] = 1
  pred_train[pred_train < 0.5] = 0
  pred_test = model.predict(test_padded_tuning)
  pred_test[pred_test >= 0.5] = 1
  pred_test[pred_test < 0.5] = 0

  acc_train = accuracy_score(pred_train, y_train)
  acc_test = accuracy_score(pred_test, y_test)
  f1_test = f1_score(pred_test, y_test, average='micro')
  print('Train : {}, Test : {}, F1_score : {}'.format(acc_train, acc_test, f1_test))
  
  if acc_train > best_scores[0][1]:
    best_scores[0][0] = (max_words, max_len, len_emb, list_pow_dense1, list_pow_dense, lr, nb_batch)
    best_scores[0][1] = acc_train
    best_scores[0][2] = acc_test
    best_scores[0][3] = f1_test
  if acc_test > best_scores[1][2]:
    best_scores[1][0] = (max_words, max_len, len_emb, list_pow_dense1, list_pow_dense, lr, nb_batch)
    best_scores[1][1] = acc_train
    best_scores[1][2] = acc_test
    best_scores[1][3] = f1_test
  if f1_test > best_scores[2][3]:
    best_scores[2][0] = (max_words, max_len, len_emb, list_pow_dense1, list_pow_dense, lr, nb_batch)
    best_scores[2][1] = acc_train
    best_scores[2][2] = acc_test
    best_scores[2][3] = f1_test

  print("-----------")

print("Meilleur taux de succs train :")
print("Combinaison : {}, Train : {}, Test : {}, f1-score : {}".format(best_scores[0][0], best_scores[0][1], best_scores[0][2], best_scores[0][3]))
print("Meilleur taux de succs test :")
print("Combinaison : {}, Train : {}, Test : {}, f1-score : {}".format(best_scores[1][0], best_scores[1][1], best_scores[1][2], best_scores[1][3]))
print("Meilleur F1_score test :")
print("Combinaison : {}, Train : {}, Test : {}, f1-score : {}".format(best_scores[2][0], best_scores[2][1], best_scores[2][2], best_scores[2][3]))

X_train, X_test, y_train, y_test = train_test_split(df_stack['Body'], df_stack['Tags'], random_state=1, test_size=0.20)

tokenizer = Tokenizer(25000, filters='')
tokenizer.fit_on_texts(X_train)
sequences = tokenizer.texts_to_sequences(X_train)
train_padded = pad_sequences(sequences, maxlen=250)
testing_sequences = tokenizer.texts_to_sequences(X_test)
test_padded = pad_sequences(testing_sequences, maxlen=250)

mlb = MultiLabelBinarizer().fit(df_stack['Tags'])
y_train = mlb.transform(y_train)
y_test = mlb.transform(y_test)

model = tf.keras.Sequential([
  tf.keras.layers.Embedding(25000, 10),
  tf.keras.layers.Dense(512, activation='relu'),
  tf.keras.layers.BatchNormalization(),
  tf.keras.layers.Dense(512, activation='relu'),
  tf.keras.layers.BatchNormalization(),
  tf.keras.layers.Dense(1024, activation='relu'),
  tf.keras.layers.BatchNormalization(),
  tf.keras.layers.GlobalAveragePooling1D(),
  tf.keras.layers.Dense(1024, activation='relu'),
  tf.keras.layers.Dropout(0.55),
  tf.keras.layers.Dense(512, activation='relu'),
  tf.keras.layers.Dropout(0.5),
  tf.keras.layers.Dense(128, activation='sigmoid')
])
model.compile(optimizer=tf.keras.optimizers.Adam(learning_rate=0.00022231214926757387), loss='binary_crossentropy', metrics=['accuracy'])
history = model.fit(train_padded, y_train, epochs=50, 
                    batch_size=64,
                    validation_split=0.3,
                    callbacks=[tf.keras.callbacks.EarlyStopping('val_loss', patience=3)])

PATH_SAVE = 'drive/My Drive/Colab Notebooks/OC/Projet 5/'

ann_ft_model = PATH_SAVE + 'ann_ft_model.sav'
model.save(ann_ft_model)

pred_train = model.predict(train_padded)
pred_train[pred_train >= 0.5] = 1
pred_train[pred_train < 0.5] = 0
pred_test = model.predict(test_padded)
pred_test[pred_test >= 0.5] = 1
pred_test[pred_test < 0.5] = 0

print('Taux de succs du train {}'.format(accuracy_score(pred_train, y_train)))
print('Taux de succs du test {}'.format(accuracy_score(pred_test, y_test)))
print('f1-score du test {}'.format(f1_score(pred_test, y_test, average='micro')))

best_scores = [[0, 0, 0, 0] for x in range(3)]

for cpt in range(20):
  print("Itration n", cpt + 1)
  list_layers = []

  max_words = random.randint(2,6)*5000
  max_words = max_words if max_words < 29000 else 29000
  max_len = random.randint(2,6)*50
  
  tokenizer = Tokenizer(max_words, filters='')
  tokenizer.fit_on_texts(X_train)
  sequences = tokenizer.texts_to_sequences(X_train)
  train_padded_tuning = pad_sequences(sequences, maxlen=int(max_len))
  testing_sequences = tokenizer.texts_to_sequences(X_test)
  test_padded_tuning = pad_sequences(testing_sequences, maxlen=int(max_len))

  len_emb = random.randint(2,4)*5
  list_layers.append(tf.keras.layers.Embedding(max_words, len_emb))

  list_pow_lstm = []
  n_layer = random.randint(0, 1)

  for i in range(n_layer):
    power2 = random.randint(7, 9)
    power = np.power(2, power2)
    list_pow_lstm.append((power, 0.05*(power2+1)))
    list_layers.append(tf.keras.layers.LSTM(power, dropout=0.05*(power2+1), return_sequences=True))

  power2 = random.randint(7, 9)
  power = np.power(2, power2)
  list_pow_lstm.append((power, 0.05*(power2+1)))
  list_layers.append(tf.keras.layers.LSTM(power, dropout=0.05*(power2+1)))
  list_layers.append(tf.keras.layers.Dense(128, activation='sigmoid'))

  lr = 10**random.uniform(np.log10(1e-4), np.log10(1e-3))
  nb_batch = np.power(2, random.randint(4, 7))

  print("Max words, len : ({}, {}), Embedding : {}".format(max_words, max_len, len_emb))
  print("List LSTM : {}, Learning rate : {}, Batch : {}".format(list_pow_lstm, lr, nb_batch))

  model = tf.keras.Sequential(list_layers)
  model.compile(optimizer=tf.keras.optimizers.Adam(learning_rate=lr), loss='binary_crossentropy', metrics=['accuracy'])
  model.fit(train_padded_tuning, y_train, epochs=50, 
            batch_size=nb_batch,
            verbose=0,
            validation_split=0.3,
            callbacks=[tf.keras.callbacks.EarlyStopping('val_loss', patience=3)])

  pred_train = model.predict(train_padded_tuning)
  pred_train[pred_train >= 0.5] = 1
  pred_train[pred_train < 0.5] = 0
  pred_test = model.predict(test_padded_tuning)
  pred_test[pred_test >= 0.5] = 1
  pred_test[pred_test < 0.5] = 0

  acc_train = accuracy_score(pred_train, y_train)
  acc_test = accuracy_score(pred_test, y_test)
  f1_test = f1_score(pred_test, y_test, average='micro')
  print('Train : {}, Test : {}, F1_score : {}'.format(acc_train, acc_test, f1_test))
  
  if acc_train > best_scores[0][1]:
    best_scores[0][0] = (max_words, max_len, len_emb, list_pow_lstm, lr, nb_batch)
    best_scores[0][1] = acc_train
    best_scores[0][2] = acc_test
    best_scores[0][3] = f1_test
  if acc_test > best_scores[1][2]:
    best_scores[1][0] = (max_words, max_len, len_emb, list_pow_lstm, lr, nb_batch)
    best_scores[1][1] = acc_train
    best_scores[1][2] = acc_test
    best_scores[1][3] = f1_test
  if f1_test > best_scores[2][3]:
    best_scores[2][0] = (max_words, max_len, len_emb, list_pow_lstm, lr, nb_batch)
    best_scores[2][1] = acc_train
    best_scores[2][2] = acc_test
    best_scores[2][3] = f1_test

  print("-----------")

print("Meilleur taux de succs train :")
print("Combinaison : {}, Train : {}, Test : {}, f1-score : {}".format(best_scores[0][0], best_scores[0][1], best_scores[0][2], best_scores[0][3]))
print("Meilleur taux de succs test :")
print("Combinaison : {}, Train : {}, Test : {}, f1-score : {}".format(best_scores[1][0], best_scores[1][1], best_scores[1][2], best_scores[1][3]))
print("Meilleur F1_score test :")
print("Combinaison : {}, Train : {}, Test : {}, f1-score : {}".format(best_scores[2][0], best_scores[2][1], best_scores[2][2], best_scores[2][3]))

X_train, X_test, y_train, y_test = train_test_split(df_stack['Body'], df_stack['Tags'], random_state=1, test_size=0.20)

tokenizer = Tokenizer(25000, filters='')
tokenizer.fit_on_texts(X_train)
sequences = tokenizer.texts_to_sequences(X_train)
train_padded = pad_sequences(sequences, maxlen=250)
testing_sequences = tokenizer.texts_to_sequences(X_test)
test_padded = pad_sequences(testing_sequences, maxlen=250)

mlb = MultiLabelBinarizer().fit(df_stack['Tags'])
y_train = mlb.transform(y_train)
y_test = mlb.transform(y_test)

model = tf.keras.Sequential([
  tf.keras.layers.Embedding(25000, 20),
  tf.keras.layers.LSTM(128, dropout=0.4, return_sequences=True),
  tf.keras.layers.LSTM(512, dropout=0.5),
  tf.keras.layers.Dense(128, activation='sigmoid')
])
model.compile(optimizer=tf.keras.optimizers.Adam(learning_rate=0.0007159028887238086), loss='binary_crossentropy', metrics=['accuracy'])
history = model.fit(train_padded, y_train, epochs=50, 
                    batch_size=32,
                    validation_split=0.3,
                    callbacks=[tf.keras.callbacks.EarlyStopping('val_loss', patience=3)])

PATH_SAVE = 'drive/My Drive/Colab Notebooks/OC/Projet 5/'

lstm_ft_model = PATH_SAVE + 'lstm_ft_model.sav'
model.save(lstm_ft_model)

pred_train = model.predict(train_padded)
pred_train[pred_train >= 0.5] = 1
pred_train[pred_train < 0.5] = 0
pred_test = model.predict(test_padded)
pred_test[pred_test >= 0.5] = 1
pred_test[pred_test < 0.5] = 0

print('Taux de succs du train {}'.format(accuracy_score(pred_train, y_train)))
print('Taux de succs du test {}'.format(accuracy_score(pred_test, y_test)))
print('f1-score du test {}'.format(f1_score(pred_test, y_test, average='micro')))
